From: Arnaldo Carvalho de Melo <acme@redhat.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Jun 2025 14:18:55 -0300
Subject: tools headers x86 cpufeatures: Sync with the kernel sources
Git-commit: d222b6e6fb31e320eca506e665694d8ddf459157 (partial)
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc3
References: perf-sle16.1-v6.19-userspace-update
X-Info: adjust for context, no (3aba0b40cacdfba4a604dd09315fa6cdbeb0ed90 ("x86/cpufeatures: Shorten X86_FEATURE_AMD_HETEROGENEOUS_CORES"), no 282cc5b6762310a73255c6dd1d79de1609042eeb ("x86/cpufeatures: Clean up formatting")
X-Info: adjust for merge commit 0939bd2fcf337243133b0271335a2838857c319f ("adding X86_FEATURE_INDIRECT_THUNK_ITS X86_BUG_ITS X86_BUG_ITS_NATIVE_ONLY")
X-Info: adjust for context, dropped X86_FEATURE_PREFER_YMM hunk from 847f1403d3ee51278dfbece84ec7f199de43daa5

To pick the changes from:

  faad6645e1128ec2 ("x86/cpufeatures: Add CPUID feature bit for the Bus Lock Threshold")
  159013a7ca18c271 ("x86/its: Enumerate Indirect Target Selection (ITS) bug")
  [not in suse] f9f27c4a377a8b45 ("x86/cpufeatures: Add "Allowed SEV Features" Feature")
  b02dc185ee86836c ("x86/cpufeatures: Add X86_FEATURE_APX")
  [not in suse] d88bb2ded2efdc38 ("KVM: x86: Advertise support for AMD's PREFETCHI")

  [missing from patch header,  also not in suse] 9a7cb00a8ff7380a ("86/cpufeatures: Define X86_FEATURE_AMD_IBRS_SAME_MODE")

This causes these perf files to be rebuilt and brings some X86_FEATURE
that may be used by:

      CC       /tmp/build/perf/bench/mem-memcpy-x86-64-asm.o
      CC       /tmp/build/perf/bench/mem-memset-x86-64-asm.o

And addresses this perf build warning:

  Warning: Kernel ABI header differences:
    diff -u tools/arch/x86/include/asm/cpufeatures.h arch/x86/include/asm/cpufeatures.h

Please see tools/include/uapi/README for further details.

